changes.new_text:
10.1 Each Party (the Indemnifying Party) shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Party, its Affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees and agents from and against any and all claims, losses, damages, liabilities, costs and expenses (including reasonable legal fees on a full indemnity basis) arising out of or in connection with:

* any breach by the Indemnifying Party of this Agreement;

* any negligent act or omission of the Indemnifying Party or its personnel;

* any defect in the Goods or Services caused by the Indemnifying Party;


* any infringement or alleged infringement of any third-party Intellectual Property Right caused by the Indemnifying Party; and

* any breach by the Indemnifying Party of any applicable law or regulation.

10.2 The indemnities in this clause 10 shall be capped at an amount equal to the fees paid or payable by Buyer to Supplier in the twelve (12) months preceding the event giving rise to the claim, save for claims arising from (a) death or personal injury, (b) fraud, or (c) wilful misconduct, which shall remain uncapped.
